    "The proposed semantic similarity measure is termed a fusion-based semantic similarity measure.To illustrate the proposed fusion-based semantic similarity measure and its comprised metrics, this section first introduces a formal description of the ontology model and definition and then describes the proposed semantic similarity measure.",
    "Ontology Model DefinitionAn ontology is defined as \"a set of representational primitives that are relevant for modeling a domain of knowledge or discourse.",
    "These primitives typically consist of a set of concepts or entities within a domain, relationships among these concepts, and attributes that distinguish each concept\" [23].",
    "A formal definition of ontology structure, as introduced by Maedche and Zacharias [31]: Definition 1 (Ontology) An ontology structure is a six-tuple O ∶=< C, P, A, H c, prop, att >, where C represents the con- cept set defined in O; P is a set of relationships defined in O, each (p ∈ P) has a domain and range which are at least one concept of the setC; A is a set of attributes defined in O; H c is a directed transitive relation H c ⊂ C × C which is also called concept taxonomy, H c c 2, c 1 means c 2 \"is- a\" c 1, or c 2 is a sub-concept of c 1; prop is a function, i.e.prop ∶ P → C × C, that relates concepts non-taxonomically, e.g.",
    "the function prop p 1 = (c 1, c 2) means that the concept c 1 is related to the concept c 2 through p 1; and att is a func- tion, i.e."
